                    </div>
                    <span>Like most women's magazines, this InStyle book makes the twisted assumption that all women hate the way they look and must "camouflage" their countless flaws. Its persistent notion that anxiety is our key motivating force is, in a word, depressing.<P>As well, in an effort to be a comprehensive primer, it tends to be patronizing and ridiculous. We KNOW what a turtleneck is, thanks.<P>I was amused to see the rave review here from "Tracy Lawton" who is obviously related to InStyle's editor, Charla Lawton. <P>Disappointing.</span>
                  
